    "actions_taken": [
      "Manual activation of Emergency Shutdown (ESD)",
      "Closure of automated Shutdown Valve (SDV)",
      "Manual closure of main burner and pilot burner valves",
      "Water spray into Burner's Flame Arrestor",
      "Fire tube removal and inspection",
      "Magnetic Particle Inspection (MPI)",
      "Weld repair and reinforcement"
    ],
    "summary": "On May 7, 2022, a fire occurred in the EAW-1000 Natural Draft Fire Tube Burner of Electrostatic Heater NBK-1000 on SS Block 193 Platform. A Burner Safety Low alarm activated at 0430 hours, and personnel observed black smoke from the heater treater stack. Investigation revealed cracked welds in the fire tube causing oil leakage into the combustion area. The fire lasted approximately two minutes and was extinguished by manual ESD activation and water spray. No injuries occurred.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Consider adjusting Heater Treater temperature when total production fluctuates",
      "Track daily temperature readings for trending purposes"
    ],
